    <div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
        <h4 class="header">Regional Status</h4>
        
            <p>We need further information to understand the relationship of this species in the state’s desert vegetation.</p>
        

        <ul class="text">
        
            <li><b>Mojave Desert</b> (322Ap). Keeler-Wolf et al. (2005) described <i>Ziziphus obtusifolia</i> stands at Joshua Tree National Park of the southern Mojave Desert along small washes. Associated shrubs were <i>Atriplex canescens, Ephedra californica</i>, and <i>Salix exigua</i>.</li>
        
            <li><b>Sonoran Desert</b> (322Bb). We have observed small stands in washes originating from the Little Maria and Palen mountains of the Sonoran Desert, which are not permanently moist. The associated shrubs were <i>Senegalia greggii, Hyptis emoryi</i>, and <i>Olneya tesota</i>.</li>
        
        </ul>
    </div>


    
	
